According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Lip Balm Market was valued at USD 215 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 230 million in 2026 to USD 327.5 million by 2032, registering a CAGR of 6.4% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing steady growth due to increasing consumer awareness of lip health, rising demand for natural and organic formulations, and growing preference for products offering hydration, SPF protection, and sustainable packaging. Beauty trends emphasizing preventive skincare, combined with innovations in plant-based ingredients and eco-friendly packaging, continue to drive market expansion across Europe.
